    stem: `A 38-year-old woman presents to your clinic for advice. She is smoker and has been on progesterone-only pills for the past 3 years. Recently, following an episode of tonic-clonic convulsion, a neurologist has started her on carbamazepine. Which one of the following would be the most appropriate advice regarding contraception?`,
