    stem: `A 16-year-old girl who is a dedicated ballet dancer is brought to your clinic by her mother for evaluation because she has not started menstruation yet. She has a body mass index (BMI) of 16 on examination. Of all secondary sexual characteristics, only breast buds consistent with a Tanner stage II are present. You order serum FSH, LH, TSH, and prolactin levels, all of which return normal. Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?`,
