    subtopic: "Primary Amenorrhea with Delayed Puberty",
    stem: `Sarah, 18 years old, is in your office for a visit because she is concerned about her delayed puberty and absence of menses. She has never had a period before. On examination, she has no pubic or axillary hair, and her breasts are at the Tanner I stage. Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?`,
