    stem: `A 34-year-old primigravida woman presents to the emergency department at 36 weeks of pregnancy after she passed approximately 200 ml of clotted blood per vagina at home 45 minutes ago. Currently, there is no active vaginal bleeding. On examination, she has a pulse rate of 120 bpm and blood pressure of 90/60 mmHg. Abdominal examination reveals a very tense uterus and moderate tenderness on palpation. Fetal heart sounds are audible at a rate of 140 bpm. Which of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?`,
