    topic: "Obstetrics & Gynaecology",
    subtopic: "Hyperemesis Gravidarum",
    stem: `A 27-year-old woman presents with severe nausea and vomiting at eight weeks of pregnancy. She cannot take solid foods but can drink small sips of liquids. She is concerned that she might have gastroenteritis because her partner has recently had it. Which one of the following is the next best investigation in this situation?`,
