    subtopic: "Preterm prelabor rupture of membranes (PPROM)",
    stem: `Chloe, 35 years old, comes to your clinic with presenting complaint of a gush of clear vaginal fluid. She is 28 weeks pregnant. On speculum examination, pre-term pre-labor rupture of membranes (PPROM) is confirmed. The cervical os is closed. In addition to transfer to a tertiary care center, which of the following would be the most appropriate management?`,
