    topic: "Obstetrics & Gynaecology",
    subtopic: "Rubella Exposure in Pregnancy",
    stem: `A pregnant elementary school teacher, aged 24, presents to your GP office after she finds that one of the students in her class has been recently diagnosed with rubella by his GP; the diagnosis, however, was not confirmed by serologic studies. Her last vaccination against rubella was when she was 12. Which one of the following would be the next best step in management?`,
