    explanation: `The following are known risk factors for spontaneous abortion or miscarriage: advanced maternal age (≥35), previous miscarriage(s), antiphospholipid syndrome, parental chromosomal derangements, embryonic chromosomal abnormalities, congenital uterine malformations, cervical weakness, diabetes mellitus (subclinical disease excluded) and thyroid disease (subclinical disease excluded), immune factors, infections, inherited thrombophilic defects, caffeine, smoking, and alcohol use (dose-dependent). A retroverted uterus has not shown an association with an increased risk of spontaneous abortions. A retroverted uterus is a uterus that is tilted backward instead of forward.`,
