    stem: `On examination of a 28-year-old nulliparous woman at 37 weeks gestation, her fundal height is found to be 35cm, and her fetus is in a transverse lie. An ultrasound exam in the 18th week revealed a low-lying placenta. Which one of the following is the most likely cause of this presentation?`,
