    stem: `A 35-year-old primigravida woman presents to your clinic for her first antenatal check-up. She is eight weeks pregnant and is concerned that her baby might have chromosomal abnormalities. She asks for antenatal screening tests. Which one of the following results at this time would indicate further assessment for trisomy 21?`,
