    stem: `Jane, 25 years old, presents to you at 14 weeks gestation and is extremely concerned because this morning, she developed a rash characteristic of chickenpox after two days of low-grade fever and mild malaise. Serology studies show positive anti-varicella IgM. Which of the following would be the most appropriate action in this situation?`,
