    subtopic: "Incarcerated Gravid Uterus",
    stem: `A 25-year-old woman presents to the emergency department at 14 weeks pregnancy with complaint of urine retention for the past 18 hours. She had an obstetric ultrasound at 10 weeks pregnancy confirming the date. In the emergency department, a transvaginal ultrasound is performed confirming the gestational age and revealing a retroverted uterus. On abdominal examination, there is a tender mass midway below the umbilicus. Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?`,
