    explanation: `When a breech presentation is suspected by manual exam, ultrasonography is needed as the next best step in management for confirmation, as well as evaluation of the maternal pelvis, fetal size, and viability. This should be considered in every future visit. The breech presentation has a chance to spontaneously turn into cephalic at 36 to 37 weeks. Once the breech position persists beyond this time, the chance of a spontaneous version reduces to 25%. It is recommended that all women with breech presentation be offered an external cephalic version provided that there is no contraindication and cesarean delivery is not indicated for other reasons. Induction of labor is not appropriate at this stage. Steroids are not indicated. Cesarean delivery is not the immediate next step without confirmation of breech position and assessment of maternal pelvis and fetal viability.`,
