    stem: `Katherine, 28 years old, presents at your office with soreness down below at 37 weeks of pregnancy. The physical exam is highly suggestive of genital herpes. She has not had such lesions before, and this is the first time she has experienced such a problem. You take swabs for PCR and culture with the results confirming the diagnosis of primary herpes simplex infection. Which one of the following would be the most appropriate next step in management?`,
