    subtopic: "Measles in pregnancy",
    stem: `A 28-year-old 10-week pregnant woman presents 24 hours after eruption of a rash, characteristic of measles. The history and exam findings establish the diagnosis with certainty. Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?`,
