    stem: `A 28-year-old woman, who is 22 weeks pregnant in her second pregnancy, presents for evaluation of a vulval ulcer. The swab taken confirms the diagnosis of herpes simplex type II (HSV-II) infection. When she is informed, she becomes quite surprised as neither she nor her husband has ever had this infection before and insists on knowing the source of the infection. Furthermore, she is very concerned about her baby's well-being and asks whether her condition may affect it. Which of the following is the most appropriate advice in this regard?`,
