    subtopic: "Cord prolapse risk factors",
    stem: `A 37-year-old woman presents to your clinic for an antenatal checkup. She has a past obstetric history of breech presentation, premature rupture of membranes, and twin pregnancy. She also had postpartum depression during her last two pregnancies, as well as anemia and gestational diabetes in her last pregnancy. Which one of the following would not increase the risk of cord prolapse during delivery?`,
