    subtopic: "Cytomegalovirus infection in pregnancy",
    stem: `A 27-year-old woman comes to your clinic at 16 weeks gestation for a review of her blood tests, which are positive for cytomegalovirus (CMV) IgM. She is asymptomatic, and the clinical examination is unremarkable. Which of the following options is the most appropriate next step in management?`,
