    topic: "Obstetrics & Gynaecology",
    subtopic: "Group B Streptococcus screening and management in pregnancy",
    stem: `A 28-year-old pregnant woman presents to your clinic at 32 weeks gestation with vaginal discharge and itching. A low vaginal swab is taken as a part of the assessment. The result is positive for group B streptococcus (GBS). No other abnormal finding is reported. Which one of the following would be the appropriate management regarding the positive GBS culture?`,
