    topic: "Obstetrics & Gynaecology",
    subtopic: "Group B Streptococcus in Pregnancy",
    stem: `Mary, 33 years old, presents to the Maternity Unit for delivery at 38 weeks gestation. She has had all her antenatal visits until now, but there is no record of Group B streptococcus (GBS) status in her file. When you discuss the issue with her, you learn that her general practitioner failed to take swabs for culture. Mary has a 3-year-old son, Michael, who suffered an early GBS sepsis shortly after birth but survived and enjoys good health now. Mary's current pregnancy has been uneventful until now. Which of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?`,
