    subtopic: "Deep Vein Thrombosis in Pregnancy",
    stem: `A 30-year-old woman developed deep vein thrombosis at 30 weeks of pregnancy and was started on therapeutic dose of low molecular weight heparin (LMWH). Now at 34 weeks gestation, she is in your office for a follow-up visit. Her expected date of delivery is due in four weeks. Which one of the following would be the best advice for her today?`,
