    topic: "Obstetrics & Gynaecology",
    subtopic: "Maternal trauma in pregnancy",
    stem: `A 28-year-old pregnant woman is involved in a car accident at 26 weeks gestation while wearing a seatbelt. On examination, there are visible bruises on the abdomen. She is otherwise normal. Fetal heart sounds are audible and within normal parameters and CTG is reassuring. Which one of the following is the next best step in management?`,
