    topic: "Obstetrics & Gynaecology",
    subtopic: "RhoGAM administration in Rh-negative pregnancy",
    stem: `A 26-year-old primigravida presented with vaginal bleeding at 16 weeks gestation. She is Rh-negative, but her partner is Rh-positive. On examination, the cervix is dilated, and the products of conception are visible. Pelvic ultrasound confirms the diagnosis of spontaneous abortion. Which of the following would be the most appropriate advice regarding Anti-D antibody (RhoGAM)?`,
